{
  "texts": [
    "We now consider LLMs in the context of the theoretical model of Probably Approximately Correct (PAC) learning, Valiant (1984).",
    "Recall that S is the set of sequences of length l in T.",
    "Consider a hypothesis space of functions F = {f: S → Y }, where for s ∈ S, f (s) is a hypothesis q s for the probabilities p s of Equation 1.",
    "We follow Shalev-Shwartz & Ben-David (2014) in defining an agnostic learning algorithm as below.",
    "As in Section 3, the training corpus T provides D sequences of length l as training samples for the learning algorithm."
  ]
}